{
  "id": "PLACE_the_saltweld_cistern",
  "label": "The Saltweld Cistern",
  "description": "The Saltweld Cistern is a basalt-bored cave in Brineshade’s uplands, its walls dark and glassy under a permanent crust of evaporite salts. Shallow basins step across the floor in terraced shelves, each rimmed with mineral blooms that record repeated cycles of brine rise and withdrawal. Narrow fissures in the ceiling admit thin shafts of hard white light that fracture through airborne haze and illuminate the cave’s granular salt drifts. The air holds a persistent mineral tang, and the stone carries faint, stress-sheared seams aligned with the planet’s tidal loading.",
